def: The insertion of a day, or other portion of time, in acalendar.
Strong nippers or a chisel for dividing bone.
To greet again; to resalute; to return a salutation to; togreet. Shak.
Whatever person; any person who; be or she who; any one who;as, he shall be punished, whoever he may be. "Whoever envies orrepines." Milton. "Whoever the king favors." Shak.

To gush or issue suddenly or violently out in a stream, asliquor from a cask; to rush from a confined place in a small streamor jet; to spirt.Thus the small jet, which hasty hands unlock, Spurts in thegardener's eyes who turns the cock. Pope.
Pertaining to the Cyclops; characteristic of the Cyclops; huge;gigantic; vast and rough; massive; as, Cyclopean labors; Cyclopeanarchitecture.
Being vertical, or at the highest point of altitude; hence,predominant. [R.]
Admonisher; monitor.Conscience is at most times a very faithful and prudent admonitor.Shenstone.
One who treats; one who handles, or discourses on, a subject;also, one who entertains.
A term applied to a lady's long, close-fitting dress made withwaist and skirt in one.
